jobDescription:
Acting Manager: Infrastructure Planning - for the month of Aug, Sept & October 2020, June, October & November 2021, Jan & Feb 2022
•To develop the ATNS CNS strategy, taking account of related global trends and developments while minimizing risk.
•	Review and implement the CNS Transition Roadmap, taking account of ICAO SARPS, other applicable statutory requirements user needs and capacity growth.
•	Prepare the ATNS CAPEX plan using inputs from other ATNS departments as regards ATM operational needs, equipment obsolescence and research and development outputs.
•	Prepare User Requirement Statement, Business cases and functional specifications for CNS systems and equipment and hand to the relevant department as per procedure for completion of tender documents and system acquisition. 
•	Determine and quantify the ATM community Infrastructure (CNS, Display and General) and ATM technology needs in area of expertise, for incorporation into ATNS Infrastructure planning and CAPEX budgeting.
•	Provide project management expertise and oversight of CNS/IT Infrastructure projects, ensuring on-time, on budget delivery without compromising high quality deliverable;
•	Taking ownership of CNS/IT projects and initiatives and bring them to a successful closure;
•	Provide periodic reporting on initiative status, activities and tasks, risk, inter-dependencies and issues for presentation to senior executives and other major stakeholders;
•	Realization of the potential for improvement through optimization of existing organizational structures and processes, as well as the introduction of new standards;

description:
Moving present dreams towards a better real future with committed ignited teams, within the socio-environmental field. Skilled in environmental awareness, empathic and efficient coordination, community & stakeholder engagement.
Clifton's top 5 strengths: responsibility, self-assurance, relator, developer, maximizer.
Founder of the first River University/Rzeczny Uniwersytet ever done, under the wings of CCB (2018); co-founder of the Save the Rivers Coalition/Koalicja Ratujmy Rzeki /KRR (2016) in Poland; co-initiator and coordinator of the first Water Round Table / Wodny Okrągły Stół in Poland on the protection of waters and rivers in cooperation with the Ministry of the Environment (2009-2011); co-creator of Partnership for The Baltic initiative (2007-2012).

Certified Project Manager PRINCE2®, also on result-based management, Governance for Transboundary Freshwater Security and global diplomacy.
Particularly interested and working in areas of #transboundary waters, #water stakeholders inclusion, #waterconflicts, #waterdiplomacy #waterdemocracy building, #problemsolving.
In 2021 nominated to Ashoka SHE SAYS program supporting women changemakers and social entrepreneurs.

Actively present in:
Coalition Clean Baltic (CCB) - where I'm focussed on inland waters and river basin management in the Baltic region environment which influence condition of the Baltic Sea;
Water working group of European Environment Bureau in terms of the water-related policy;
Save The Rivers Coalition (KRR) - Polish national coalition dedicated to rivers/water protection where I'm oriented on Odra basin and I'm an observer of ICPO;
Friends of Ina and Gowienica Rivers Society (TPRIiG) [www.tpriig.pl] - regional level of riverine activity where I'm engaged in practical and educational projects;
International Commission for the Protection of the Odra River against Pollution (ICPO) as an NGO observer

You may also find some bits of me here: www.researchgate.net/profile/Ewa_Les
